Year = {2018},
Pages = {405-421},
Abstract = {The role of the Graduate Teaching Associate (GTA) can be critical to
   supporting the work of teaching centers and may provide graduate
   students with a path into educational development (ED). At a time when
   many graduate students will not find traditional, tenure-track faculty
   positions, we must begin to examine how these teaching center roles can
   prepare graduate students for future ED work and what we can do to help
   them transition into a position in the field. Through a collaborative
   auto ethnographic approach, this chapter explores three educational
   developers' journeys into ED and how the profession can begin to
   systematically prepare graduate students for a career in ED.},
