Volume = {29},
Number = {1},
Pages = {88-100},
Month = {JAN 2},
Abstract = {In response to calls to revisit the engagement of students in academic
   development, the authors - an educational development consultant and a
   graduate student - share the findings of a nation-wide study which
   explored how Canadian teaching and learning centres (TLCs) partner with
   graduate students in academic development (AD). This paper highlights
   the benefits and challenges identified by the participants and draws on
   students-as-partners (SaP) literature to frame the recommendations and
   lessons learned about how to engage graduate students meaningfully and
   ethically in AD activities. We share pragmatic strategies while
   emphasizing the importance of aligning partnerships with the SaP
   principles of respect, reciprocity, and responsibility.},
